CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 17, 1959, pg. 3 reads: "Office Entrance - This is the entrance to the office of Dr. James E. Brown, located at 6293 Frankstown Ave.  Notice his name on the door.  Dr. Brown also owned this building which served as a medical center for East End physicians for many years. - Harris Photos"
TitMainTitle: Exterior of the office of Dr. James E. Brown, on 6293 Frankstown Avenue with geometrically patterned tile and striped awning
